Does not do as advertised. Will not allow me to select a folder to display photos from randomly. It only lets you choose one photo at a time. Can I please get a refund?
Great! Does the job

I bought this app because I wanted to display random photos from specified folders. The problem is the app does not allow you to select a folder. This problem has been referred to by other reviewers but the app developer has not fixed the problem. Specifying a folder is one of the advertised features of the product. It does not work. Other features listed in the app do appear to work but the one I want does not
Trash lots of features but what good is that when the pisture quality is a blur. and i paid for this. won't my money back.
can't chose folder in SD card
Love this app.

I purchased this full version some time ago and used it fine after the 6.0 update. But today one of the widgets disappeared, and when I make a new one I am unable to make a folder selection. The folder tree view appears but is blank. This persisted through a restart. Is there any way to get support?

I loved this app as it allowed me to see my baby's pictures right on the main screen. It allowed them to flip through. But now, it constantly freezes my phone, sometimes for minutes. When it does that, it renders the phone useless. I cannot get into it or if I am in something else, it will stop. Also, I keep having to add the widget back onto my screen. It keeps disappearing and will freeze even when not up. I have given up at this point and think I need to uninstall, after purchase.
Can't explore folders to be selected for photos in android 7 on Nexus 5x.
Works perfectly, does what every other photo widget does, however i like that it doesn't crop the images, they remain to scale.
The free one works but ads pop up!
I need the image to stay in the same prientation but instead it auto rotates.

What I've been looking for, I love the search options but I keep getting repeated pictures. An option to go to the page an image is found on would be very handy! Lost 2* because the image search options don't work. Lost another * for lack of updates
Mostly great. Freezes and needs to reboot sometimes. I think that it may have lead to my SD card becoming nonfunctional though, so uninstalling.
A little pricy for the new features but it does what it says and it's what I want it to.
This app does everything I wanted it to do and more. Love the slideshow setting. Great to see different pics of my dogs every time I boot up the phone.
Most of the pictures are rotated 90 degrees one direction or the other. Very frustrating.  I even rotated the original pictures to compensate but it did not help.  Droid Turbo
What can I say, it's rare to find an app these days the does exactly what it says on the tin.. Can't fault it, paid for and got x
I was very disappointed in this widget. Extremely slow, not the way I wanted to view my photos.
Not bad, better than most that I have tried but please make availability of more Time changing setting's and will be perfect
In battery stats this app uses more battery than everything but the screen.
There is no other photo frame widget like this! Works flawless. Lots of settings. Love it!
I've had this app since, I think, the original Droid. Every once in a while I'll go looking for a better photo widget, but just keep coming back!
almost perfect - plz add blacklist button (to prevent pics from show up again) and a save button. super app!
Recent updates take this from 4 to 5 stars. Thanks.
Love this widget! Been using it for years. Hope the developer integrates it with the Google daydream feature.
I have used this widget with all the phones that I have had. I like the app very much.  I look for this app every time I have to re-download my apps.   Thank you.

Either the app or?android 4.2.2 has stoped the free or paid version from working. When chosing a single image file the app goes into a continous loop. It is like it forgets the file chosen and just keeps asking you over and over and over. Tried ubinstalling and reinstalling to try and fix. Didnt work. Real bunnrr as i had liked it so much i bought it. But now its broken. Bummer as i used it alot on customizing my tablet screens. Please fix it!
I paid for this were is the update.
RIP widget.

I bought the paid version for the Picasa integration, which works, but needs to be better. App requires you to enter your password and does not support two factor authentication, so an application specific password must be used. So far, just a little annoying. What really got me is that the password must be re-entered each time a new instantiation of the widget is created. But for that, I would rate higher.
Faultless. This won't be uninstalled any time soon!
Had free version for a while. Finally got around to trying what I wanted to do and it does the job. Decided to get paid version to help support devs. Thanks folks.
This is an excellent widget with exactly the right functionality, but I'd love some larger or fully resizeable versions for my 10" Galaxy Note.
The best
Nice, but for images from Picasa it needs your credentials. You need to implement some OAuth. I don't want to provide credentials of my Google account, sorry.
Exactly what I was looking for and works wonderfully!
Freezes my SGSII if I try to make any changes.
with Galaxy Nexus running ICS

Finally a photo frame that doesn't auto crop photos. I had a bunch of photos that I wanted to not have to edit. All other photo viewer widgets automatically crops photos and most you can't stop. If u want a simplistic photo viewer widget give this one a go! Has a free version too.
Works well. Need an option to change pictures more frequently than 15 second.

Does exactly what it says. Some options I'd like to see: presets - being able to setup some preset  slideshows, depending on your mood, would be a great addition. As it stands, going into settings to select a different folder is cumbersome.  Would also like to see the tap options a little larger, for those of us with fat fingers.  Update 11-4-12: I'm revising my review. I've come across a few problems. The settings don't seem to be saved. I'll choose a folder and options, including turning recursive off. After an undetermined amount of time, the recursive option turns itself on. And when I try to turn it off, the app forces closed, and all options revert back to the defaults. I've knocked this down from 5 stars to 3, because of this problem, and because the authors do not respond to emails. This isn't a free app, so some support is expected.

Love this product! Would like to see two minor features to make it a five. How about a shorter update frequency? For such small pictures, I'd prefer 5 seconds. And the second, being about to rotate to landscape when viewing landscape photos so they are bigger. Thanks for a great product and I'm more than happy that I bought it.
Works ok for a few days then dies...DON'T WASTE YOUR CASH. HTC sensation
Love it however:  Can't enter more than one item in image search. Did not accept my Picasa credentials.  I contacted them by email, let's see how long it takes for a reply.
I don't believe this works on the Nexus 7. Disappointment.
Like the frame selection a lot. Great job.
Does what it should do accept for one issue.  It ignores picture rotation so portrait photos are not displayed correctly. At least from a selection of iPhone photos. If fixed super.
Keeps force closing and freezing. Frame selection is very limited.

I have tried wifi and cell connection but still cannot verify license.  If you want to make your app this much trouble at least improve it a little.   Image quality could certainly be better on some images.
Also sets a completely useless icon in your app drawer. Better free options available.
It does what it says but the resolution of the pics are quite low on my Nexus.  Makes nice pics looks blurry. Barely usable without improvement in resolution.
Would be super amazing but it crashes every time I try to put the change time on 15 seconds
Can't zoom, can't size to fit frames, can't google search.   Not worth the cost.

Can't choose any specified folder (HTC one x)

I have ran across a small bug though been using this for over 3 months and I love it. I've used the thin white border and sometimes after a long sleep it is thicker. Thought it was the pic but its not. Still this works very well
Please add bigger sizes for tablet use.  Otherwise, no 4 or 5 star rating.  I can even deal with the non-tablet optimized menu, just bigger sizes please.
Doesn't take some files.  No pinch-zoom option.  Poor support.

I used the free version for awhile and it worked great, but I wanted a 3x3 frame and more photos in the slideshow.  If you have the free version you need to uninstall it to get this version to work properly (you can uninstall it after you install this version).
Using on xoom tablet ics 4.0.4 and Galaxy Nexus ics 4.0.4

Galaxy note:  Works good, just needs more sizes and frames. Try the free one first.  Also photos come put the wrong rotation, only way to fix is open in picsay, save the pic, and use the picsay pic. This will open it the correct angle.
Choosing frame works great first time but crashes if you change it. Polaroid frame just gives a vertical stripe with no photo

Works well enough. Has a force close bug when changing frame, but this is easily worked around. After a while searching this is my favourite picture viewing widget due to ease of use and the variety of sizes available (including 3x2). Not sure why the developer didn't think to mention the sizes in the description... Also do not count on ANY support from the dev. I recommend downloading and check it does what you need it to do. If not, get an instant refund via the market.
Works good but force closes when editing an existing frame. Feature Suggestion: Add picture change on phone unlock. Samsung Galaxy Prevail
Best one I've purchased! It would be great if you could make the images "still" :)
I wish I could rotate the image into landscape instead of portrait mode all the time. Once fixed, I will rate higher!... DROID x.
Google search type of pic or site name results are used as slideshow in widget that auto resizes to fit pics.  Perfect!  dsc streak gingerbread
Stay away. Poorly written, buggy, licensing doesn't work... DISASTER!!
Stunning on HTC Flyer. Has all the options I want and works beautifully. You can choose to have no frame if you want, which I prefer. Twice as many 5-star ratings as any other says it all.
works swell , great for slideshows
